A chieftain of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Kwara state Yakubu Gobir has Muslim faithful to use this period of Ramadan to call on God for protection, especially given the insecurity plaguing the country. Gobir, who is also the Madawaki of Ilorin added that “as we approach the 2023 election, let the wishes of the common men, women, and youth on the street be met.”   Buhari prays for peace during Tasfir     Don’t mock Allah with Ramadan, Olubadan charges Muslims     Ramadan: Yobe reviews curfew time by one hour   He congratulated the Muslim faithful on the commencement of the Ramadan. In a statement, the chairman of the Gobir Foundation expressed gratitude to God, while also supplicating for forgiveness of sins and a rich reward for piety during the fasting period.